2.0.0
=====
Initial version of the refactored Niddel App for Splunk. Main changes:
* Will now use the Niddel Magnet v2 API to interact with the back-end for configurations and other settings,
AWS credentials no longer need to be configured;
* Alert download logic moved to a separate add-on (https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3710/), which was built
with the Splunk Add-on Builder and also uses the Niddel Magnet v2 API to access the alerts;
* Refactored dashboards with improved content;
* Updated to reflect the breaking changes in alert format, which now conform to
https://api.niddel.com/v2#/definitions/Alert;
* Separated credential configuration, which requires a Splunk admin user, from the log collection setup.
This will make it possible for non-admin users that belong to a new `niddel_admin` role to fully configure
the log collection;
* Completely refactored normalization, filtering and aggregation saved searches and macros for simplicity and
performance and a renewed focus on firewall and web proxy logs.
